Kalra,

As far as I know, vegan has the only DCA implementation in R similar to the
original DECORANA. You cannot use that for partial or constrained detrended
analysis. This would require changing the original Fortran code which in
turn requires a good knowledge of the original design of the function and
cannot be done casually. I have no plans to make the changes needed for
partial or constrained DCA.

I abstain from commenting the use of DCA in estimating gradient lengths (but
don't recommend anybody to do so).

Cheers, Jari Oksanen


